WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.620 --> 00:00:11.150
 350 kilometers above Earth. 

00:00:12.520 --> 00:00:19.010
 Average speed: 7.7 kilometers per second. 

00:00:20.170 --> 00:00:26.900
 90 minutes are needed for a complete rotation around the Earth. 

00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:35.000
 The sun rises and sets every 45 minutes. 

00:00:36.200 --> 00:00:42.900
 The International Space Station has been on a low orbit around the Earth since 1998. 

00:00:43.850 --> 00:00:50.800
 It is used as a research laboratory for biology, physics, astronomy and meteorology. 

00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:58.850
 The International Space Station is constantly growing. 

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:06.700
 During the mission, new modules have been added. 

00:01:08.100 --> 00:01:14.900
 In 2014, the mass of the station reached 420 tons. 

00:01:15.950 --> 00:01:22.800
 The ISS, including its large mirrors, covers an area equal to that of a football stadium. 

00:01:24.100 --> 00:01:30.800
 The station is often visible to the naked eye from Earth ... 

00:01:32.100 --> 00:01:38.900
 ... even during the day. 

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:54.700
 (Virtual video speed: 146 kilometers per second) 

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:28.500
 (Actual Speed ​​of the International Space Station: 7.7 kilometers per second) 

